article.headline: Old Dominion 79, East Carolina 53
article.story: NORFOLK, Va. (AP) -- Isiah Hunter scored 20 points, including 4-of-5 3-pointers, to lead Old Dominion over East Carolina 79-53 on Saturday. The Monarchs (5-1) jumped to a 37-23 halftime lead over the Pirates (3-2), who were led by Corey Rouse's 14 points and nine rebounds. ODU's Arnaud Dahi finished with 16 points Alex Loughton added 12 points and 10 rebounds. Courtney Captain was the only other Pirate in double figures, with 12.
